div1.p:
The law having confided to the Department and Secretary 
of Labor authority to hear and determine this matter, the 
decision by the Secretary as to every question involved 
is conclusive, and the record of the hearing maybe examined 
by the court in this proceeding only to determine whether 
the hearing contemplated by the statute has been allowed
and whether at said hearing some evidence has been secured 
tending to support the adminstrative decision.
- Ekin v. United, 142 U.S. 650, 35 L. Ed. 1146; 
- Kamataya v. Fisher (Japanese Immigrant Case) 189 U.S. 86, 47 L. Ed. 721;
- United States v. JuToy, 198 U.S. 253, 49 L. Ed. 721; 
- Chin You v. United States, 208 U.S. 8, 52 L. Ed. 369; 
- See also Lem Moore Sing v. United States, 158 U.S. 538, 39 L. Ed. 1082.
